{"questionId":"6350","questionHtml":"<p>The mass of the Earth is <em>M</em><sub>E</sub> and the mass of the Moon is <em>M</em><sub>M</sub>. Their respective radii are <em>R</em><sub>E</sub> and <em>R</em><sub>M</sub>.</p>\n<p>Which is the ratio&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{escape speed from the Earth}}}}{{{\\text{escape speed from the Moon}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>escape speed from the Earth</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>escape speed from the Moon</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{{M_{\\text{M}}}{R_{\\text{M}}}}}{{{M_{\\text{E}}}{R_{\\text{E}}}}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>M</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>M</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>E</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>E</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{{M_{\\text{E}}}{R_{\\text{E}}}}}{{{M_{\\text{M}}}{R_{\\text{M}}}}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>E</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>E</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>M</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>M</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{{M_{\\text{E}}}{R_{\\text{M}}}}}{{{M_{\\text{M}}}{R_{\\text{E}}}}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>E</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>M</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>M</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>E</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{{M_{\\text{M}}}{R_{\\text{E}}}}}{{{M_{\\text{E}}}{R_{\\text{M}}}}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>M</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>E</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>E</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>M</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"6350","referenceCode":"18M.1.HL.TZ2.32","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The mass of the Earth is ME and the mass of the Moon is MM. Their respective radii are RE and RM. Which is the ratio escape speed from the Earth escape speed from the Moon ? A. M M","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"32","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.2 – Fields at work","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}